com.ibm.team.process.common

Interface IProcessConfigurationElement


  • public interface IProcessConfigurationElement
    A process configuration element is a node in a tree of element. Each element has exactly one parent and may have one or more children. An element that represents the root of a tree does not have a parent. An element has a potentially empty set of named attributes. The value of attributes is accessible via the attribute name.
    Since:
    0.5
